	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />You might try asking this over on the forums at NESWorld.
<br />
<br />I know Martin (site owner + Famicom/NES collector) has made some similar labels in the past (mainly just images for the 'net though), so he might be able to shed some light on the matter.
<br />
<br />Admittedly, I don't see how this can be all that difficult.  Getting high-quality scans of some of the standardised crap (i.e. Nintendo's seal of approval) really isn't that hard.  Scan, apply a couple default Photoshop filters, clean up some of the borders/edges, adjust brightness/contrast to make up for scanner quality, and voila.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


